'''''The Girl's Guide to Depravity''''' is a comedy/drama series based on [[Heather Rutman]]'s popular blog of the same name. The show debuted in the US on Cinemax as part of its soft-core block Cinemax After Dark in February 2012 and has aired internationally in Latin America (HBO), Spain (Cuatro), Canada (IFC), and Japan (Dentsu).

==Premise==
Based on a blog,<ref>{{cite web|title=Cinemax Category|url=http://thegirlsguidetodepravity.com/category/cinemax/|publisher=TheGirlsGuidetoDepravity.com|accessdate=1 June 2012}}</ref> ''The Girl's Guide to Depravity'' is about two women, Lizzie (Sally Golan) and Samantha (Rebecca Blumhagen) and the rules they use to have fun and avoid being hurt in relationships.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Girl's Guide to Depravity: Extras|url=http://www.cinemax.com/after-dark/the-girls-guide-to-depravity/cast-crew/#/after-dark/the-girls-guide-to-depravity/extras/|publisher=Cinemax|accessdate=1 June 2012}}</ref>

